HEADWORD: Zygophyllum
<hw>Zy`go*phyl*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A genus of usually tropical herbs or shrubs having ill-smelling
foliage and flower buds that are used as capers: bean capers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus Zygophyllum.</syn>⟦br⟧
